ad made my child do i removed him straight away and made a serious complaint about the school. &#10;now no mainstream school is accepting my son they by law have to contact his previous school and when they do the headmaster tells them my son is this uncontrollable nightmare, he isent hes a child with different needs!. &#10;so now no local mainstream schools are willing to take my son on, he has a spinal problem epilepsy some behaviour issues (hes currently waiting to be assesed by cahms becouse his previous school think hes autistic, personnally i just think they want to stick a label on him). &#10;all these schools are refusing my son without even meeting him wich really angers me.&#10;i want my son to go to a mainstream school as i,m worried in a special needs school his education will fall further behind. &#10;i dont know what to do plz help"/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1136" language="en" documentId="4877" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="joanne m(387)" date="19-08-12 18:37" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://www.netmums.com/coffeehouse/advice-support-40/special-needs-disabilities-support-502/809172-fighting-keep-my-son-mainstream-school-all.html" topic="mainstreaming" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="4877" notes="" title="fighting to keep my son in mainstream school"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="83"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="84" end="176"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="177" end="394"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="395" end="616"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="617" end="893"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="59" sofa="1" begin="894" end="979"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="63" sofa="1" begin="980" end="1104"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="67" sofa="1" begin="1105" end="1136"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51 55 59 63 67"/></xmi:XMI>